.TH "virt_to_scatterlist" 9 "virt_to_scatterlist" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
virt_to_scatterlist \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" virt_to_scatterlist
.BI "(const void *addr "  ","
.BI "int size "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *sg "  ","
.BI "int sg_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
Virtual address
.IP "size" 12
Size of data; should be an even multiple of the block size
.IP "sg" 12
Pointer to scatterlist array; set to NULL to obtain only
the number of scatterlist structs required in array
.IP "sg_size" 12
Max array size
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Fills in a scatterlist array with page references for a passed
virtual address.

Returns the number of scatterlist structs in array used
